President Bush plans to nominate Zalmay Khalilzad, the ambassador to Iraq, to be the American ambassador to the United Nations. Mr. Bush wants Ryan C. Crocker, the ambassador to Pakistan, to replace Mr. Khalilzad in Baghdad. Meanwhile, Mike McConnell, a retired vice admiral who once led the National Security Agency, is Mr. Bush's choice to assume the post of director of national intelligence. And Harriet E. Miers, the White House counsel who was briefly one of Mr. Bush's Supreme Court nominees, said she was leaving the administration.
PAGES A3, A6 AND A14
